President Trump has declared a major disaster in Kentucky due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for federal funding to be provided to the Commonwealth and eligible local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, to support emergency protective measures. Gracia B. Szczech has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.